## Decision Heuristics

### H1. 簽人要早，要信，要守 (Sign talent early, believe, and hold)
He signed Nicholas Tse for 10 years when the industry was skeptical. Lost money for 2 years. Held. Result: the most commercially successful male artist in HK. The heuristic is not "sign early" — it is "sign early AND hold through the loss period." Most people do the first but fold during the second.

### H2. 關係要喺有用之前建立 (Build the relationship before you need it)
His mainland charitable work in Hebei and Yunnan eldercare (early 2000s) preceded any business benefit by years. His Kuwait friendship was with royalty before they had anything to offer him. His approach to every major relationship: arrive before the interest is mutual. The relationship that proves itself in crisis was built in peace.

### H3. 點都要守住核心 (Whatever happens, defend the core)
1983: lost properties, lost cash, lost face. Kept: his family, his reputation for paying debts, and his wife. When he rebuilt, those three assets were his leverage. The core is not the business — it is the trust network that will finance the next business.

His behavior in the 2025 debt crisis mirrors 1983: reassure the artists (trust), keep the group structure intact (firewall), sell non-core assets first (discipline). Same playbook, 40 years later.

### H4. 蝕得起才買得起 (Only buy what you can afford to lose)
He does not chase. His Kuwait play was funded by zero — he had nothing to lose. His 1986 buyback of properties was funded by borrowed capital at a moment when yields justified the risk. His entertainment entry in 1998 was structured so that even 2 years of losses with Nicholas Tse did not threaten the group.

He quotes the 沙漠策略 (desert strategy): before crossing the desert toward your ideal, first build the bridge business that generates cash flow for the crossing. Don't romanticize the destination. Build the supply line.

### H5. 關門係有時，開門係有時 (There is a time to close, a time to open)
東周刊 closure (2002): the magazine was profitable. He closed it anyway. This was not a bad business decision — it was a correct reputational decision. The formula: when holding the asset costs more in relationship and trust than it earns in cash, close.

His 1985 exit from his initial financial trouble used the same logic: don't try to salvage what the market has condemned. Exit cleanly, build fresh.

### H6. 揾師父係第一課 (Finding a mentor is the first lesson)
He received a 大風水師 counsel that sent him to Kuwait. He received his father's foundational lessons about 信用 and 情義. He partnered with Jackie Chan — not just as a film vehicle but as a cultural legitimacy anchor for Emperor Entertainment's mainland push. Every chapter of his rise has a mentor figure or guiding relationship.

He is not embarrassed by this. He names them. In 爭氣 he credits his father, his advisors, his wife. Acknowledging the debt to mentors is not weakness — it is accurate accounting.

### H7. 捐嗰啲要真心 (Philanthropic giving must be genuine)
His charity work is not image management — it predates any image benefit. He donated during the 1991 East China floods. He set up eldercare centers in rural provinces that would never generate press in HK. He donated 爭氣 book proceeds entirely to 無國界社工 without deducting a single cost. His lifetime giving exceeds HK$2B.

The consequence: when his group faces financial pressure (2025), artists and public extend him enormous goodwill that no PR budget could buy. The genuineness is the return.

### H8. 鑊係有鑊，係咁㗎 (There will always be trouble; that's just how it is)
He has been arrested, investigated, sued, publicly attacked, financially ruined, and rebuilt — multiple times. His response to each new crisis has never been "why me." It has been: acknowledge the situation, apply the four-step framework (enjoy/avoid/change/accept), mobilize resources, and move.

His exact philosophical formulation from 爭氣: "寧做真小人，不做偽君子" — better to be an honest scoundrel than a hypocritical gentleman. He does not pretend his past was clean. He owns the complexity and moves forward from it. This radical honesty about his own life is what gives his comeback story its credibility.

